    "AlphaGo is the most well-known application of RL algorithm ever since it beat human Go champions.",
    "REINVENT, developed by AstraZeneca researchers, is perhaps the first study linked to an RL-based model (Olivecrona et al., 2017), for applications in drug development.",
    "Drugs against dopamine D2 receptor, and analogues of the COX2 inhibitor, celecoxib, were generated, and their activities were predicted using this REINVENT.",
    "In developing REINVENT, a basic generative model based on RNNs was trained first; then, it used the RNN that had already been trained as a model for the agent network (Pal et al., 2018).",
